Package eu.profinit.manta.connector.powerdesigner.model

Interface DataModel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    NamedObject, eu.profinit.manta.dataflow.generator.modeling.common.nodes.NodeMetadata
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConceptualDataModel, LogicalDataModel, PhysicalDataModel
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataModel, ConceptualDataModelImpl, LogicalDataModelImpl, PhysicalDataModelImpl
    public interface DataModel
extends NamedObject
    A data model is a representation of the information consumed and produced by a system, which lets you analyze the data objects present in the system and the relationships between them. PowerDesigner provides conceptual, logical, and physical data models to allow you to analyze and model your system at all levels of abstraction. A data model in PowerDesigner is mapped one to one with a file where it is stored. Every specific data model has to extend this so it can be casted to this common predecessor.
    Author:
    ddrobny
